joy /dʒɔɪ/

(joys) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Joy is a feeling of great happiness. 高兴 

例： Salter shouted with joy. 索尔特高兴地叫起来。 

2. N-COUNT A joy is something or someone that makes you feel happy or gives you great pleasure. 使人高兴的事; 使人高兴的人 

例： Spending evenings outside is one of the joys of summer. 在户外消磨晚间时光是夏天的乐事之一。 

3. PHRASE If you say that someone is jumping for joy , you mean that they are very pleased or happy about something. 兴高采烈 

例： He jumped for joy on being told the news. 听到这个消息他兴高采烈。

